35 regulations with the joint committee on agriculture for review and comment at least 30 days
36 before the effective date of the policies, rules or regulations.
37 (f) The secretary shall file a quarterly report with the house and senate committees on
38 ways and means, the joint committee on agriculture, and the clerks of the house and the senate
39 on the following: (i) a list of grant applicants and the counties in which they are located, (ii) list
40 of grant recipients and the counties in which they are located, (iii) the amount of funds requested
41 by applicants, (iv) the associated grant amounts, (v) the applicantâ€™s sector as categorized by farm
42 or fishery, (vi) an annual statement detailing the sources and uses of funds, (vii) a forecast of
43 future payments based on current binding obligations, and (viii) a detailed breakdown of the
44 purposes and amounts of administrative costs charged to the fund. The report shall include a
45 description of technical assistance services provided as part of this program.
46 SECTION 2. Section 1 shall take effect immediately upon the passage of this act.
